flowchart LR
  Browser["Browser client\n(single origin)"]
  API["FastAPI REST\n/api/*"]
  RT["Backend Socket.IO\npath /socket.io/ ns /rt"]
  SSE["Backend SSE\n/api/stream/*"]
  SFU["Media Socket.IO\nengine path /rtc/ ns /sfu"]
  TURN["coturn STUN/TURN"]
  RTP["DTLS/SRTP media path"]

  Browser -->|login, sessions, history, admin| API
  Browser -->|chat, presence, annotations, media-state| RT
  Browser -->|dashboard/admin/analytics live feed| SSE
  Browser -->|join room, create transports, produce, consume| SFU
  Browser -->|gather ICE candidates| TURN
  Browser <-->|audio/video/screen media| RTP
  RTP <-->|routed by mediasoup| SFU

  %% All HTTP/WS rides the page's own origin; nginx routes by path prefix.
  %% /rtc/ is the engine.io HTTP path that nginx rewrites to the media /socket.io/.
